<figureCitation id="135E2A6A940BFFD1BE913B4DFA99FEF7" box="[1177,1284,327,349]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–6" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1849,1873]" captionTargetBox="[204,1380,194,1814]" captionTargetId="figure-32@16.[195,1392,181,1825]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 5–6. M. planipennis (5), M. quadrinus (6). 5a–b: habitus (LT); 5c–e: median lobe of aedeagus in ventral (c), dorsal (d) and lateral (e) view [0.7 mm]; 5f: sclerites of endophallus [0.4 mm]; 5g: spermatheca [0.3 mm]; 5h: antenna [1.1 mm]. 6a–b: habitus (LT); 6c–e: median lobe of aedeagus in ventral (c), dorsal (d) and lateral (e) view [0.6 mm]; 6f: sclerites of endophallus [0.4 mm]; 6g: spermatheca [0.3 mm]; 6h: antenna [1.0 mm]. scI–IV: sclerites I–IV of endophallus. Square brackets: length of scale segment." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6443775" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6443775/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="255">Figs 5e, 6e</figureCitation>
